# Troubleshooting

## Authentication Failed

```
remote: Invalid username or token.
```

Cause:

- GitHub no longer supports password authentication over HTTPS.

Solution:

- Use SSH authentication.
- Or use a Personal Access Token (PAT).

---

## Permission Denied (publickey)

```
Permission denied (publickey)
```

Verify the key is loaded.

```bash
ssh-add -l
```

If no identities are listed:

```bash
ssh-add ~/.ssh/git_ssh
```

or

```bash
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
```

---

## Verify SSH Configuration

```bash
cat ~/.ssh/config
```

Example:

```text
Host github.com
    HostName github.com
    User git
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/git_ssh
    IdentitiesOnly yes
```

---

## Verify Permissions

```bash
chmod 700 ~/.ssh
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/*
```

---

## Check Git Remote

```bash
git remote -v
```

Should display:

```
origin git@github.com:user/repository.git
```

---

## Test SSH Verbosely

```bash
ssh -vT git@github.com
```

This displays detailed debugging information if authentication fails.

