# Useful Commands

List loaded keys

```bash
ssh-add -l
```

List SSH files

```bash
ls -la ~/.ssh
```

Show public key

```bash
cat ~/.ssh/git_ssh.pub
```

or

```bash
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```

Check Git version

```bash
git --version
```

Check Git configuration

```bash
git config --global --list
```

---

# Security Best Practices

- Never share your private SSH key (`git_ssh` or `id_ed25519`).
- Only share the public key (`*.pub`).
- Protect private keys with appropriate file permissions (`600`).
- Consider using a passphrase for your SSH key.
- Regularly review and remove unused SSH keys from your GitHub account.

